.TH "hfi1_make_rc_req" 9 "hfi1_make_rc_req" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hfi1_make_rc_req \- construct a request packet (SEND, RDMA r/w, ATOMIC)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hfi1_make_rc_req
.BI "(struct rvt_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "struct hfi1_pkt_state *ps "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qp" 12
a pointer to the QP
.IP "ps" 12
the current packet state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Assumes s_lock is held.

Return 1 if constructed; otherwise, return 0.
